Nine people have tested positive for COVID-19 at the Lebombo border post with Mozambique. The border post Manager Obe Maditsi says the positive cases were mostly detected from South Africans travelling home after the holidays. The number of people who have tested positive for COVID-19 at the Lebombo border post is now close to 20 after another nine tested positive yesterday. According to the Lebombo Border Post Manager, Obe Maditsi, South African nationals who test positive are transported to Nutting House in Mbombela for quarantine while non-South Africans are turned back. The number of coronavirus cases in the country is increasing. The new variant is playing a significant role in the spread of the virus. An explanation of what the new variant is:  Yesterday 11 859 new coronavirus cases were recorded in the country bringing the total number to 1 100 748. More people are also dying of COVID-19 complications. South Africa recorded 402 deaths yesterday, most of which were in the Eastern Cape. Below are the latest coronavirus stats in SA: COVID-19 STATISTICS IN SOUTH AFRICA sabcnews.com |  SABC News Channel | SABC Radio news SOURCE: Department of Health  & ﻿National Institute of Communicable Diseases  CASES GAUTENG WESTERN CAPE KWAZULU-NATAL EASTERN CAPE FREE STATE LIMPOPO NORTH WEST MPUMALANGA NORTHERN CAPE 213 473 173 592 27 489 38 541 UNALLOCATED 0 AS AT 03 JANUARY 2021 7583 615 656 DEATHS 2187 7195 5727 4642 577 CONFIRMED CASES| 1 100 748 DEATHS | 29 577 TESTS CONDUCTED | 6 742 853 RECOVERIES | 903 679 395 86163 298 068 41 459 25 913 218 679  Free State  North West  Gauteng  Mpumalanga  Northern Cape Eastern Cape  Limpopo  KwaZulu-Natal Western Cape 63 534 (function(d){var js, id="pikto-embed-js", ref=d.getElementsByTagName("script")[0];if (d.getElementById(id)) { return;}js=d.createElement("script"); js.id=id; js.async=true;js.src="https://create.piktochart.com/assets/embedding/embed.js";ref.parentNode.insertBefore(js, ref);}(document)); Health Minister Zweli Mkh